<DocsLayout title="Installation">
  <h1>Installation</h1>

  <p>
    Coral supports Python 3.8+ and can be installed via pip or from source.
  </p>

  <h2>From PyPI (Recommended)</h2>

  <pre><code># Basic installation
pip install coral-ml</code></pre>

  <h2>Optional Dependencies</h2>

  <p>Coral has several optional dependency groups for different use cases:</p>

  <pre><code># PyTorch integration
pip install coral-ml[torch]

# S3/MinIO storage backend
pip install coral-ml[s3]

# Hugging Face Hub integration
pip install coral-ml[huggingface]

# Development tools
pip install coral-ml[dev]

# Everything
pip install coral-ml[all]</code></pre>

  <h2>From Source</h2>

  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/parkerdgabel/coral.git
cd coral
pip install -e ".[dev,torch]"</code></pre>

  <h2>Using uv (Recommended for Development)</h2>

  <pre><code># Install uv if you haven't
curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh

# Clone and setup
git clone https://github.com/parkerdgabel/coral.git
cd coral

# Install with all dev dependencies
uv sync --extra dev --extra torch</code></pre>

  <h2>Verify Installation</h2>

  <pre><code># Check CLI is available
coral-ml --help

# Or in Python
import coral
print(coral.__version__)</code></pre>

  <h2>Dependencies</h2>

  <h3>Core (Required)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><code>numpy>=1.21.0</code> - Array operations</li>
    <li><code>h5py>=3.0.0</code> - HDF5 storage</li>
    <li><code>xxhash>=3.0.0</code> - Fast content hashing</li>
    <li><code>tqdm>=4.60.0</code> - Progress bars</li>
    <li><code>networkx>=3.1</code> - Version graph management</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Optional</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><code>torch>=1.10.0</code> - PyTorch integration</li>
    <li><code>boto3>=1.26.0</code> - S3 storage backend</li>
    <li><code>huggingface-hub>=0.19.0</code> - HF Hub integration</li>
    <li><code>safetensors>=0.4.0</code> - Efficient weight loading</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
